00:02:56.980 --> 00:02:59.100
Or you could say, this
is 0 minus negative 5.

00:02:59.100 --> 00:03:01.200
This distance right
over here is 5.

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:04.030
This distance is the
distance between 0 and 5

00:03:04.030 --> 00:03:04.840
in the y direction.

00:03:04.840 --> 00:03:05.920
That's 5.

00:03:05.920 --> 00:03:08.180
Pythagorean theorem tells
us that 5 squared, which

00:03:08.180 --> 00:03:11.710
is 25, plus 5
squared, another 25,

00:03:11.710 --> 00:03:14.090
is going to be equal to
your hypotenuse squared.

00:03:14.090 --> 00:03:15.659
And that's exactly
what we have here.

00:03:15.659 --> 00:03:17.450
Now, you might be
saying, wait, wait, wait,

00:03:17.450 --> 00:03:19.520
this thing had a
negative 5 squared here,

00:03:19.520 --> 00:03:20.924
while here, you
had a positive 5.

00:03:20.924 --> 00:03:23.340
But the reason why we could
do this is when you square it,

00:03:23.340 --> 00:03:24.624
the negative disappears.

00:03:24.624 --> 00:03:26.290
The distance formula,
you could write it

00:03:26.290 --> 00:03:28.410
this way, where you're
taking the absolute value.

00:03:28.410 --> 00:03:30.410
And then, it becomes very
clear that this really

00:03:30.410 --> 00:03:31.860
is just the Pythagorean theorem.

00:03:31.860 --> 00:03:34.260
This would be 5
squared plus 5 squared.

00:03:34.260 --> 00:03:35.844
5 squared plus 5 squared.

00:03:35.844 --> 00:03:37.510
The reason why you
don't have to do this

00:03:37.510 --> 00:03:39.700
is because a sign doesn't
matter when you square it.

00:03:39.700 --> 00:03:42.760
It always will become
a positive value.

00:03:42.760 --> 00:03:45.360
But either way, we
figured out this radius.

